theorem
Th4: (( rng c ) = { x0 } implies (((c is  convergent & ( lim c ) = x0) & ( h + c ) is  convergent) & ( lim ( h + c ) ) = x0))
proof
assume A1: ( rng c ) = { x0 };
thus c is  convergent;
x0 in ( rng c ) by A1,TARSKI:def 1;
hence A2: ( lim c ) = x0 by SEQ_4:25;
A3: h is  convergent by FDIFF_1:def 1;
hence ( h + c ) is  convergent by SEQ_2:5;
( lim h ) = ( 0 ) by FDIFF_1:def 1;
hence ( lim ( h + c ) ) = ( ( 0 ) + x0 ) by A2,A3,SEQ_2:6
.= x0;
end;
